romWeb?topicID=3421.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ToV quests</span><hr size=1> As far as I know all the pieces are no drop. My guild has some members keeping them and the recipients of an MQ will be decided when we kill Doze. <p><center><image src=http://members.aol.com/_ht_a/jayrj1/Fironasig.jpg><Br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=133603>My Profile</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uazndailow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AznDailow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 7:18:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3421.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ToV quests</span><hr size=1> I can't comment on the pieces dropped by Dozekar, but the other pieces seem to be pretty random. We had one person in the guild get all the pieces for the Silver Bracelet of Speed in one clearing, while another needed multiple clearings. Yes, the pieces are no drop, and I'm pretty sure Lenindara the Keeper (outside exit in West ToV) is the quest giver. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucaebesilverfish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caebe Silverfish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 806<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 7:47:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3421.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ToV quests</span><hr size=1> by chance how do you guys decide who gets what?<br><br>seems that since it would be kind of rare to get at the mobs, you'd want to get somebody 'done' with what they have started.  (i.e. if they win 'x' piece, continue to award that person pieces as they continue to drop vs. taking that person out of the rolls for additionally pieces as they dropped)<br><br>regards,<br> <p><html><p align="center"><font color="#FFFFFF" size="5"face="Edwardian Script ITC"><strong>Caebe Silverfish</strong></font><br><font color="#FFFFFF" size="3"face="Baskerville Old Face">59th Season Knight of Mith Marr<br>House of Requiem<br>Tribunal Server</font></p></body></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/29/02 7:40:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3421.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ToV quests</span><hr size=1> The Dozekar method mentioned above seems to be the best way to me...our guild is just collecting pieces as we get them, we aren't &quot;awarding&quot; them as they drop.  <br><br>Since every quest needs a Dozekar drop, that's probably the best time to decide who gets something.  Otherwise you may end up with lots of people with bits and pieces of quests that could actually be made into quest reward items if people put their pieces together.<br><br>Aalek<br>60 Crusader<br>Reign in Power <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showPrevMessage?topicID=3421.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpala